%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22GitHub%20CEO%20says%20Microsoft's%20memo%20about%20evaluating%20AI%20use%20is%20'totally%20fair%20game'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Thomas%20Dohmke%2C%20CEO%20of%20Github%2C%20speaking%20at%20the%20Digital%20Life%20Design%20(DLD)%20innovation%20conference.%20DLD%20is%20a%20conference%20on%20internet%20trends%20and%20developments%20in%20digitalization.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6890f3963d5881a51c1e8fda%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThomas%20Dohmke%2C%20CEO%20of%20Github%2C%20speaking%20at%20a%20conference.%3Cp%3EReuters%2FDPA%20%2FPicture%20Alliance%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThomas%20Dohmke%2C%20CEO%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgithub%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGitHub%2C%20%3C%2Fa%3Esaid%20that%20managers%20should%20evaluate%20employees'%20AI%20usage.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDohmke%20was%20asked%20about%20an%20internal%20Microsoft%20memo%20that%20said%20using%20AI%20is%20%26quot%3Bno%20longer%20optional.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20said%20all%20GitHub%20employees%20must%20use%20GitHub%2C%20and%20if%20they%20don't%20want%20to%2C%20there%20are%20%26quot%3Bother%20tech%20companies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ECompany%20culture%20now%20includes%20thinking%20about%20AI%20use%2C%20at%20least%20according%20to%20one%20tech%20leader.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20recent%20episode%20of%20the%20%26quot%3BDecoder%26quot%3B%20podcast%2C%20GitHub%20CEO%20Thomas%20Dohmke%20defended%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMicrosoft%3C%2Fa%3E%20memo%20that%20asked%20managers%20to%20evaluate%20employees%20based%20on%20how%20much%20they're%20using%20internal%20AI%20tools.%20Business%20Insider%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-internal-memo-using-ai-no-longer-optional-github-copilot-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20memo%20in%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20in%202025%2C%20it's%20totally%20fair%20game%20to%20say%20you%20should%20reflect%20on%20your%20AI%20usage%2C%20and%20you%20should%20reflect%20what%20did%20you%20learn%20about%20AI%2C%20did%20you%20use%20GitHub%20Copilot%20or%20Microsoft%20Copilot%2C%20Teams%20Copilot%20to%20summarize%20a%20meeting%2C%20and%20if%20not%20why%20not%3F%26quot%3B%20Dohmke%20said%20on%20the%20episode%2C%20which%20aired%20August%207.%20GitHub%20is%20Microsoft's%20software%20development%20platform%2C%20and%20GitHub%20Copilot%20is%20an%20AI%20coding%20assistant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20the%20memo%20was%20%26quot%3Bmore%20nuanced%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Btalked%20about%20AI%20learning%26quot%3B%20in%20a%20conversation%20between%20a%20manager%20and%20employee.%20That%20learning%20process%2C%20he%20said%2C%20aligns%20with%20Microsoft's%20growth-oriented%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOriginally%20sent%20by%20Julia%20Liuson%2C%20the%20president%20of%20a%20Microsoft%20division%20responsible%20for%20GitHub%20Copilot%20among%20other%20developer%20tools%2C%20the%20memo%20said%20that%20AI%20usage%20should%20be%20part%20of%20managers'%20%26quot%3Bholistic%20reflections%26quot%3B%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-plans-potential-rethink-performance-reviews-pivot-satya-nadella-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eemployees'%20performances%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAI%20is%20now%20a%20fundamental%20part%20of%20how%20we%20work.%20Just%20like%20collaboration%2C%20data-driven%20thinking%2C%20and%20effective%20communication%2C%20using%20AI%20is%20no%20longer%20optional%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20core%20to%20every%20role%20and%20every%20level%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20reads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDohmke%20said%20that%20GitHub%20employees%20have%20a%20specific%20non-negotiable%3A%20using%20GitHub.%20His%20expectation%20applies%20not%20just%20to%20developers%20but%20to%20every%20division%2C%20from%20HR%20to%20sales%20to%20legal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20world%20where%20I%20would%20allow%20for%20somebody%20to%20say%2C%20'Well%2C%20sorry%2C%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20use%20GitHub.'%20And%20I%20think%20that's%20fair%20game%20if%20the%20employee%20doesn't%20want%20that%2C%20then%20there's%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20other%20tech%20companies%20out%20there%20where%20they%20can%20have%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it's%20part%20of%20our%20company%20culture%20that%20everybody%20at%20GitHub%20uses%20GitHub.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Dohmke%2C%20measuring%20AI%20usage%20doesn't%20mean%20assessing%20how%20many%20lines%20of%20code%20someone%20wrote%20with%20AI%2C%20since%20that%20metric%20is%20%26quot%3Beasily%20gamified.%26quot%3B%20Instead%2C%20he%20said%20it's%20about%20demonstrating%20a%20mindset%20that%20aligns%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fatt-ceo-memo-workplace-loyalty-dead-employees-job-security-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecompany%20culture%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgithub-ceo-thomas-dohmke-microsoft-memo-tracking-ai-use-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1754927437000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F689a0d01a17a8c5b4052a3dd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgithub-ceo-thomas-dohmke-microsoft-memo-tracking-ai-use-2025-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Thomas%20Dohmke%20also%20said%20that%20GitHub%20employees%20should%20use%20GitHub%2C%20and%20if%20they%20don't%20want%20to%2C%20%26quot%3Bthere's%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20other%20tech%20companies.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22atecotzky%40businessinsider.com%20(A