t%20at%20Moody's%20Analytics.%3Cp%3ETom%20Williams%2FCQ-Roll%20Call%2C%20Inc%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMoody's%20economist%20Mark%20Zandi%20recently%20warned%20that%20the%20US%20economy%20is%20on%20the%20%26quot%3Bprecipice%26quot%3B%20of%20a%20recession.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOver%20the%20weekend%2C%20he%20shared%20more%20insights%20as%20to%20how%20we'll%20know%20if%20a%20recession%20is%20here.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EEconomist%20Mark%20Zandi%20thinks%20the%20US%20economy%20is%20on%20the%20brink%20of%20a%20recession%2C%20and%20there%20are%20a%20few%20signs%20he%20says%20that%20will%20show%20one%20has%20arrived.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20delivered%20his%20dire%20warning%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-recession-economy-tariffs-immigration-policy-jobs-data-bls-trump-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20state%20of%20the%20economy%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20week%2C%20and%20followed%20it%20up%20over%20the%20weekend%20with%20a%20series%20of%20posts%20on%20X%20about%20what%20he's%20eyeing%20to%20know%20if%20the%20economy%20has%20tipped%20into%20a%20downturn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20topic%20of%20recession%20is%20heavily%20debated%2C%20with%20economists%20consistently%20deliberating%20over%20what%20qualifies.%20While%20the%20US%20is%20not%20yet%20in%20a%20technical%20recession%E2%80%94defined%20as%20two%20straight%20quarters%20of%20negative%20growth%E2%80%94other%20areas%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjuly-jobs-report-unemployment-rate-employment-federal-reserve-interest-rates-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20labor%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20sounding%20a%20warning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZandi%20noted%20in%20his%20post%20that%20historically%2C%20the%20answer%20to%20exactly%20what%20signifies%20a%20recession%20is%20not%20always%20clear%20until%20after%20circumstances%20have%20shifted.%20However%2C%20in%20the%20thread%2C%20he%20laid%20out%20a%20few%20key%20factors%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPayroll%20employment%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEmployment%20levels%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EJob%20decline%20consistency%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20the%20National%20Bureau%20of%20Economic%20Research%20(NBER)%20is%20considered%20the%20arbiter%20of%20when%20a%20recession%20begins%20and%20ends%2C%20noting%20one%20key%20factor%20that%20its%20academic%20researchers%20consider%20above%20others.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20they%20look%20at%20a%20plethora%20of%20data%20to%20make%20this%20determination%2C%20most%20importantly%2C%20far%20and%20away%2C%20is%20payroll%20employment%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20stated%2C%20adding%20that%20if%20employment%20falls%20for%20more%20than%20a%20month%20consecutively%2C%20the%20economy%20has%20entered%20a%20downturn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZandi%20said%20that%20payroll%20employment%20has%20not%20fallen%20yet%20but%20added%20that%20it%20has%20barely%20increased%20since%20May%2C%20which%20he%20seems%20to%20find%20troubling.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%26quot%3BGiven%20that%20the%20recent%20revisions%20to%20the%20jobs%20numbers%20have%20been%20consistently%20lower%2C%20much%20lower%2C%20it%20wouldn't%20be%20surprising%20if%20we%20learn%20with%20the%20coming%20revisions%20that%20employment%20is%20already%20declining%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20second%20factor%2C%20Zandi%20raised%20the%20point%20that%20employment%20is%20falling%20throughout%20many%20industries.%20He%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FMarkzandi%2Fstatus%2F1954544462555648142%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20previously%2C%20if%20half%20of%20the%20400%20industries%20being%20surveyed%20reported%20declining%20employment%2C%20an%20economic%20recession%20had%20begun.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20cited%20recent%20data%20that%20revealed%20that%20in%20July%202025%2C%20more%20than%2053%25%20of%20industries%20reported%20job%20cuts%2C%20with%20only%20the%20healthcare%20sector%20showing%20employment%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%2C%20unemployment%20is%20a%20lagging%20indicator%20and%20given%20that%20the%20labor%20force%20has%20gone%20sideways%20this%20year%20as%20the%20number%20of%20foreign-born%20workers%20is%20declining%2C%20unemployment%20will%20be%20a%20particularly%20poor%20barometer%20of%20recession%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZandi%20concluded%20that%20the%20US%20economy%20is%20still%20not%20in%20a%20recession%2C%20as%20evidenced%20by%20the%20job%20decline%20factor.%20%26quot%3BA%20recession%20is%20defined%20by%20a%20persistent%20decline%20in%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20the%20decline%20lasts%20for%20at%20least%20a%20few%20months%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20aren't%20there%20yet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20the%20economic%20tides%20could%20shift%20if%20policy%20weighs%20on%20growth.%20In%20his%20previous%20post%2C%20Zandi%20said%20that%20Trump's%20policies%2C%20mainly%20tariffs%20and%20immigration%2C%20are%20the%20big%20drivers%20of%20his%20view%20that%20the%20economy%20is%20teetering%20at%20the%20edge%20of%20a%20downturn.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fis-the-us-in-recession-jobs-unemployment-mark-zandi-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1754926148000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6899fca3cfc04e97619b2d9c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fis-the-us-in-recession-jobs-unemployment-mark-zandi-2025-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Mark%20Zandi%20laid%20out%20why%20he%20thinks%20the%20US%20economy%20is%20on%20the%20brink%20of%20a%20recession.%20For%20clues%20about%20when%20a%20downturn%20could%20hit%2C%20look%20to%20the%20labor%20market.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sobrient%40insider.com%20(Samuel%20O'Brient)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fis-the-us-in-recession